High frequency of trolling lure shanks and points associated with offshore fishing for pelagic species in phases 1, 2, and 3. Evidence for a sharp decline in the importance of offshore fishing for pelagic species during phase 3 (first decades of 15th cent) or shortly afterward.
This interpretation is supported by results of the fish bone analysis, with a frequency of pelagic fishes around 25 to 35% in phases 1/2/3 (before 15th c) and sharp fall off under 8% in phases 4 and 5 (16-19th c).
